HEADWORD: Shaps
<hw>Shaps</hw> <pr>(sh⟦acr⟧ps)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[Shortened
fr. <ets>chaparajos</ets>. Cf. <er>Chaps</er>.]</ety>
<def>Chaparajos.</def> <mark>[Western U. S.]</mark></p>

<p><q>A pair of gorgeous buckskin <qex>shaps</qex>, embroidered up the
sides and adorned with innumerable ermine skins.</q> <rj><qau>The
Century.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

